    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/931: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-11T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 11, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 11—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Our 16, June 10, 6 p.m.<note n="45" xml:id="d454fn45">Not printed.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">London Times</hi> further reports that another amendment to
                    the Industrial Control Bill confers extraordinary tariff powers to the
                    President. Its account of the nature of these powers is incomplete, kindly cable
                    full text.</p>
                <p>In the light of these two additions to the Industrial Control Bill or any other
                    new tariff or similar restrictions does the President see <pb facs="0734"
                        n="632" xml:id="pg_632"/> any obstacle to the introduction of the tariff
                    truce resolution? I would appreciate a full interpretation either by immediate
                    cable or by telephone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
